>
  <h1>Disclosure</h1>
  <p>
    We participate in affiliate programs for some of the tools we review. When you click a tracked link and make a purchase, we may earn a commission at no extra cost to you. These links are marked <code>rel="sponsored"</code> in our HTML.
  </p>
  <h2>How this does not affect reviews</h2>
  <p>Editorial decisions — what we cover, our ratings, and what we recommend — are independent of affiliate status. We have published critical reviews of affiliate partners and recommended free alternatives over paid ones we earn from.</p>

  <h2>Current affiliate relationships</h2>
  <p>The following programs are active. This list is reviewed quarterly:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>(Placeholder) — example.com</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>FTC compliance</h2>
  <p>This site complies with the U.S. Federal Trade Commission's <em>Guides Concerning Use of Endorsements and Testimonials in Advertising</em> (16 CFR Part 255). Every page with affiliate content includes a disclosure or links to this page.</p>

  <h2>What we don't do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Accept payment to publish or boost a review</li>
    <li>Let vendors review drafts before publication</li>
    <li>Run "sponsored content" disguised as editorial</li>
  </ul>
</ProseLayout>
